4</rating>
< Text>
Unloaded in 30mins, plenty of room to back into docks. Just circle around the building to check in. Receiving is by dock #10. Getting back to freeway is little tricky since there is devider in the middle. Make a right on canal blvd, then first right on Ohio street go about 2 miles, another right on Harbor, then it will take you straight to the ramps. Not to sure if they will let you park on premises for over night. You can always park on street no signs.< /Text>

<Rate>3< /Rate>< text>
I love the drinks and the food was very good,  however the service wasn't the best, the waiters weren't attentive as they should.  I would call on one and she'll be like "where is your waiter to help you?" After telling her, I haven't seen in 40 minutes, she then took my order... so that is the downfall, you gotta wait until being serve and enjoy the food/drinks.</text>

< review>
Second time here and still dissapointed. They pour heavy on the chamoy sweet sauce. You don't even taste the beer. The service is slow and had to flag down servers several times.

They may call themselves the house of micheladas but these are just chamoy with chili drinks. Completely different taste that what you are used to.

Cheers!< /review>

This is a little gem in La Habra area. It is located inside a strip mall . It was very cozy and nice place with a superb services. This restaurant was very clean and the foods were excellent . I tried a spicy seafood noodle  it tasted so delicious and authentic. Loved the bean sprouts and kimchi here. We also ordered a king dumplings and chicken noodle soup. <time>1559549513103</time>< rating>
5</rating>
<Text>If you are looking for a location with spicy food, this is the spot to go! They are one of my favourite Chinese restaurant that makes me sweat as I eat.

My favourite dish is the spicy fish and the tofu one. The spice added to the fish gives it a rich flavour. The tofu on the other hand is so silky and soft. My dad the outside is tofu and the egg is inside, but nonetheless it is so delicious.

Depending on the time frame, it can get packed!! For my bday, I came here at 6PM and there was at least 20 people waiting outside. It look about 30-40 minutes to be seated for us. Keep in mind I came at dinner time so it was expected to be crowded.

Parking is free, and the lot is huge. If you don‚Äôt find spot in the parking lot, just drive to the market parking next lot. However you should be fine since their lot is pretty decent.<//Text>< Pics>

Chili King used to be great with Hunan flavor profile. Now, the  menu has been revamped. it's not as large as it used to be. I think the chef and the owner is different. last time, we went there the servers were eating lunch as we were eating. Waiter smoke outside the door. Food is going downhill. (Original)
The owner of Pepper King Hunan Cuisine Restaurant (Chilli King) has very poor service and is grumpy. When he takes a big order, he doesn't care about small customers. He often insults guests and the driver who receives the meal.  It may be that the business is so good, the boss is rich, and he speaks very well!  I am really worried about the quality of the food, this kind of service really hurts the hearts of the guests and the driver! I concluded that Pep Boys tried to rip me off as I was driving to a different state, which shows poor integrity and makes me distrust them greatly.< /Review>

This review is about a year late but Dr. Kahlon is awesome and knows what he is doing. Took in my 10 year old pup because he stopped getting up/moving. Although they were very busy and I didn't have an appointment Luis spoke to the vet and the doctor decided to see us anyways he examined him and ordered x-rays and he knew right away he had arthritis prescribed some medication and within a day or two my dog was back to normal!
Forward to another year I have another dog who needed dental extractions and took her in for an estimate. Although it was pricey I knew it needed to be done and warned him about my dogs prior complications with anesthesia (a different vet I took her to for dental extractions said she stopped breathing and had to do CPR so he couldn't continue the procedure, he probably didn't know what he was doing) Dr. Kahlon didn't have any problems with her anesthesia thankfully! Both my dogs have been treated by him and both are doing well and fully recovered :)

{'time': 1604279083245, 'text': "Dear Carol,\n\n4 years old Daisy was seen twice here for being painful on her back . We recommended radiographs, complete blood cell count and chemistry last time. You declined all diagnostics and we sent home a NSAID and a muscle relaxant at that time. We followed up with you and you reported she is doing much better. The visit at that time cost you less then $100.\n\nYou brought her back again recently for the same reason and this time you wanted to get all diagnostics done which were declined last time. The blood work showed mild elevation of ALT but everything else was unremarkable. She was still painful and sensitive to palpate on her back. We sent home the same medications like last time and recommended you that you should get bile acid testing done to rule out liver disease. You made an appointment for it the next day, but you never showed up. Mild elevation of ALT is sensitive but not specific for liver disease. Daisy had normal AP, albumin , bilirubin , slightly elevated (instead of lower) BUN and GGT levels but still due to her having history of seizures we wanted to rule out a liver shunt/liver disease and this is why we recommended bile acid testing. We are not sure at this point why she started vomiting on this medication few days afterwards , when you have administered this same medication last year without any issues. Vomiting in dogs can be due to so many different reasons including as simple as getting into or eating something they are not supposed to.\n\nIt's true radiographs can't confirm Intervertebral disc disease but they are done to rule out obvious bony changes/decreased intervertebral disc space. Since radiographs did not show any abnormal obvious changes , we recommended MRI scan. I understand this is a lot of information and can be overwhelming at times when you are concerned about the well being of your fur baby. Please call us anytime if you have any questions or concerns."}< /resp>

<Name>Mike Brown< /Name>< Text>
We were looking for a new vet that is closer to our home and after doing some research decided to take our dog to All Valley Pet Hospital for a check up and vaccinations. I think that it was a great choice!  I was impressed at how friendly the front desk staff was. I was also impressed with the Vet tech cum hospital manager Analisa as she was friendly, knowledgeable and instantly connected with my dog, who was a bit skittish at first. We saw Dr Kahlon and he was great!  He was able to quickly gain my dog's trust, performed a thorough examination and took the time to explain the reasons for dog food allergies. He was very up front about his recommendations and at no time did I feel that he was in a rush to get us out of there. Dr Kahlon is the new owner and full time veterinarian at All Valley,I learnt. I look forward to having Dr Kahlon take care of our veterinary needs! Thank you so much All Valley Pet Hospital!< /Text>

<gmap_id>0x80ec6ca865483465:0x888a38827297645c< /gmap_id>< review>
Dr. Kahlon has a very strong accent that makes it hard to understand. He sold me a supplement that cost $48 as if it were a prescription. I found the very same supplement online for $28! I was pretty sure my cat had a UTI but he started telling me it could be diabetes or FIV or....  I was scared for my poor cat and I should have just insisted that they test her urine first. I came out of there with a $250 bill for all sorts of tests pluse the stupid supplement for $48 and all she has is a UTI! They called and left a message the next day to tell me everything came out negative except for the urine and that I had to call and then go in to pick up the antibiotics for her UTI! When I called, the receptionist didn't know anything about it and told me she would have the doctor call me when he got back from lunch. I told her that I didn't want to talk to the doctor I just wanted to pick up the antibiotics. I am outraged! I will never, never go here again or will I recommend this place to anyone. $300 + who knows how much for the antibiotics for a cat's UTI !
Well $44 for the antibiotic and I had to wait 30 minutes for it because they wouldn't make it until I was there.... If I could give a negative 5 stars I would!< /review>
< Response>
{'time': 1582859793205, 'text': 'Hello Camille,\n\nThank you for your feedback. We apologize for the delayed response here. From what you wrote on here it seems you understood really well what the veterinarian was trying to explain(excuse his accent). Yes underlying causes of UTI in cats can be diabetes,kidney disease or  FeLV/FIV. If we were to just treat a UTI with antibiotics and not address an underlying cause, infection can keep coming back. We are glad the veterinarian recommended the right thing for your cat and did all tests after your approval and signed estimate. We are also happy the tests came back all good except for urine test which showed infection. We apologize that you had to wait in the lobby to get the medication ready because it has to be reconstituted with water and once reconstituted with water its good only for 2 weeks. It has happened with us in the past clients would call for a prescription to be filled which sometimes never gets picked up. So this policy is in place for all medications that need to be reconstituted with water before dispensing and we make it when clients actually show up to pick it, to avoid wastage.'}</Response>

< Text>
Look for the OC Mix sign and park. Enter the building and the pathway is split into a Y (cross way). Walk towards your right side and Birdie is all the way down the hall.

I got the Classic and asked for toasted coconut ($1 more). It tastes amazing and cold.

Nice shop with friendly customer service. A bit over price in my opinion. I do enjoy their classic and pitaya colada bowls. I love the toasted coconut so I always ask for extra for a $1 more. This is the spot to eat when you don't want anything too heavy or you been eating heavy food the last few days and you want to cut down on carbs but still feel energize.

They have some benches to eat and chill or you can take your bowl on a walk enjoying your healthy bowl and checking out their vendors.

I would definitely like my friends/family out here for a health light meal.<//Text>

<Review>Conveniently located inside a hipster mall with open seating near other restaurants and boutique stores. The pitaya (fancy name for dragonfruit, I believe) was good, although the fruits on top were a bit sour. They offer a bottle of honey for customers for drizzling sweetness to their hearts content. The price was above your normal strip mall located fruit bowl place, but I expect that's because Birdie probably sources better ingredients.  I also appreciate that the bowl is primarily pitaya (or acacia) and not yogurt. I don't remember if I read the word organic or local though, but I also didn't do much research beforehand on this spot, as I was invited for a meeting here. All in all, if I'm in the area and craving juice or fruit bowl, I'd consider coming here again, if only to check out the coffee shop too.<//Review><pics>None</pics>< resp>

< Review>
Danish Herring Substitute found. Has great herrings from Blue Hill Bay. They are not Danish but just as good. Add 3 heeping teaspoons white sugar to the wine sause and and dill heerings. Stir gently. Let soak for a couple of days. Viola, just like herrings from Denmark but cheaper and fresher. The kryddersild, Matjes, are ready to go without sugar. Only substitute I have found in the US that are any good.< /Review>

< Review>
We went here for dinner on Sunday night at the Irvine Spectrum. I ordered the chicken marsala and mushrooms over bowtie pasta. My son had the bang bang chicken and shrimp. Both meals were good. The best part of our meal was the dessert. I had the banana cream cheesecake which was great. My son had the rieces pieces peanut butter cheesecake. His was great also but a much different style. My cheesecake was light and his was very dense. Both were amazing. To start we also had an egg roll sampler which was surprisingly good. Our waitresses were excellent.</Review>

<Text>My boyfriend and I were celebrating an anniversary and as introverts, we wanted to explore something new and go eat somewhere we have never been.
When we walked into this place, the first thing we saw were 5 of the waitresses on their phones gather up and none of them looked at us or offered us help.
I walked up to the counter and asked for a table and she led us to a nice table with a nice view.
Unfortunatley, the silverware and the cups were pretty messed up. Im not sure if they treated us this way because we ordered water instead of everything else she offered. They didnt even give us straws, drinking out of those cups just felt wrong. She brought us some really hard bread, I whacked the table with it and it was so hard that the bread dented. She said that was all they had but when they got more, she would bring us fresh bread. Never happened.
It took her half an hour to actually get back and take our order. I asked her for the birthday cheesecake to go and she marked it down.
Took about another half hour to get our food. Luckily we had pretzel bits we bought before actually eating.
The plates were very good looking and my pasta was great, but my boyfriends Miso Salmon wasnt great at all. We waited about an hour after eating to finally get the check, she kept avoiding us. <Review>In the OC this is my favorite Cheesecake Factory. Date night do Fashion Island bar for sunset n romance, but for a nice let your hair down meal? Spectrum for sure... Had a 10/10 meal here. Seated off a walk-in reasonable 5min wait. TIP *** They get very busy here, reservations recommended. We did the early dinner trick and they looked 1/3 full already on a THUR night. Barkeep came by to ask if we were thirsty, we paused to order @ the table. It was a scorching hot day so my friend and I split plate the whole meal. Avocado toast starter, mushroom n spinach on cauliflower blend crust keeps the carbs down for flat bread pizza. Mains was a cool salmon salad over more spinach, we're not kelp fans and the kitchen was very nice to sub ingredients. Generous portion for fish and avocado as well. Service was very professional but not stuffy, very helpful. Let us chat and came by frequent for tea refills, fresh plates, setups if needed. Very comfortable service, feel bad I forgot servers name, very nice guy. His/hers restrooms were convenient at the back of the room we were in. I also love the decor at this location. Price 2.5 out of 4 stars even, that's including the drinks and a split slice of very delicious cheesecake. When in Rome, right? When done here we strolled a bit through the alleys of the mall. Quite a nice afternoon.< /Review></record></dataset><record>

<Text>I am from Seattle and had eaten at Cheesecake Factory out there and liked their food and vegetarian options. I was expecting the same level of quality when I went with family to celebrate my dad's birthday. However they did not have many vegetarian options for entrees. This was because unlike their Seattle branch all their pasta is made in chicken stock and can't be made with vegetarian stock instead. They offered to use a marinara but I was looking forward to having the same veg mushroom pasta I do in Seattle. I decided to order a veggie burger instead and that was even more sad. It had no flavour as such and the patty just fell apart and all the rice grains were seperated. They really need to look at McDonslds or Burger King in India to learn how to make a good vegetarian burger. Very very very sad.

My dad ordered a steak and he also felt the steak was really poor for the standard they make you expect. He prefers the steak he had at BJs.

The staff member was very nice and she cared a lot about our experience, sadly the kitchen couldn't back her up.

< Review>
The food was great. HUGE portions and great taste.

The low rating is due to the service I got from whom I believe was the manager (since he was the only one wearing a tie). After waiting for 15-20 minutes for my check, I decide to go talk with someone at the front desk. I tell this man that I'd like to pay my bill, and he condescendingly replies, "okay? where is your bill?" I told him I've been waiting for a while and didn't see my waiter to ask for a check. Then he replies, "okay, which is your table?" expecting me to have an answer as if I knew the exact table number. I gave him a direction, but of course, that isn't going to be precise. He then begrudgingly asked me to take him to where my table was.

The food may be the best in the world, but with staff like this, it would make me very uncomfortable to dine here again.<//Review>

On January 14 2017 we went to this restaurant and it was Saturday night around 9 pm. we waited for our table for like 20 30 minutes which is understandable because the restaurant it is in Irvine Spectrum and it is always crowded. After we waited so long they gave us the smallest table in the restaurant which was surprising but we were okay and we already waited and we were hungry so we did not want to change our table. we ordered cheese burger and chicken sandwich and we both ate 1/3 of each our foods because we had an appetizers as well too. I asked our server "RACHEL N" to bring us some boxes so we can take our foods home and she said she is going to put our food into boxes for us which was really nice of her. We paid for our foods and we took the boxes to our house, next day we opened the boxes so we can eat them and we saw it was completely different foods. We were really surprised and on Monday 16th of January I called cheesecake factory and I talked to "ANNI" who was the manager of store and when I explained everything she was like this is so strange and I have to talked with "RACHEL N" and I will call you back. <Rate>5</Rate>< Text>
Went for our 1st time last night. We had 2 Servers, Zach and Jeremy, and they were off the charts friendly !!! Dinner and appetizers were delicious...and our desserts were amazing. Items we ordered were: Tex Mex Eggrolls, Avocado Eggrolls, The Impossible Burger, Vegan Cobb Salad, Fettucini Alfredo, and Steak and Salmon Combo. Try their dinner salad!....I love their house vinaigrette. The atmosphere is fun. It's cool that you can see the Chefs in the kitchen...Beautiful Decor!! The place was packed, and the wait time was 30 min, but we walked around the mall so fine went by fast.  It was worth the wait ! :) p..s  I'm hoping they get one or two Organic items on the menu in the future, but at least they have the Impossible Burger which is delicious (even if you're not a Vegan)<//Text>

<username>Shannon Bartnick</username>< date>

<rating>3</rating>< Text>
Now I never right reviews because it isn't worth my time and not to mention I have worked in the Restaurant Industry for 15 Years and in every position you can think of so I know where people are coming from when they make mistakes, but I have been to this place twice now and both times I was extremely disappointed.  I use to love The Cheesecake Factory.
First time we went there, we were told it would only be a 45 minute wait which isn't too bad on a Saturday night, but an hour and a half later without anyone even talking to us we finally said something to them.  At this point they said we were next but decided to sit 4 other parties instead and then cram us into a small table when we have a stroller with a baby.  When we asked to sit at another table they stated that we could just place her in the aisle.  First of all if you have ever been here you know that two people can barely walk down the aisle together it is so small, not to mention I am not putting my newborn baby in the aisle to have items spilled on her. Then the food comes out and everything was wrong, so we sent it back and it came out wrong again!  I really don't feel like going into the details of everything but they were simple mistakes that shouldn't have happened twice.
Second time we went here we didn't even sit down we just placed a ToGo Order.  First of all the people didn't even seem like they knew what they were doing and then the person taken the order didn't seem like she was really even listening to us.  It took forever to get the order in, she repeated it like 3 times and then when we asked about getting a couple of drinks we were told that we needed to go to the bar.  I understand that you need to repeat the order at least one time to ensure that it is exactly what the guest wants but she was asking questions every time she repeated it.  At this point we were irritated but were hungry and didn't even care, so we waited almost 30 minutes for our ToGo food and when we got home the order was all messed up!  These are simple mistakes and after repeating the order 3 times you would think that they would have checked to make sure everything was correct.  Now I know that it might have not been the server's fault, it could have been the alley coordinator or the runner who sometimes assists or other servers / managers whatever, but come on people!!!  There is a BIG difference between Fries and Sweet Potato Fries!</Text>

<rating>1< /rating><Text>Worst dinning experience EVER! Worst customer service experience EVER! Worst lies told by a manager EVER! Worst trained personnel EVER!
Food delivered to table late and cold,
No utensils
Asked several helpers and waiters but no response (ours was nowhere to be found)
Got up to get utensils and was told to sit down.
10 minutes later utensils arrive and we start eating cold food
Manager arrives and actually starts shouting at us for disturbing the servers and making too many requests!?? Really?? Where was he trained?? Servers are meant to serve the customers, and I had food but nothing to eat it with!! For OVER 10 MINUTES!!
Anyway, was never allowed to get in a word edge wise by the manager.
After he left, and several other diners sitting near us told us how appalled they were to see us being treated that way after having had such poor service. They were shocked as much as we were and said they would never eat there again. None of them left tips since they wanted management to understand what they did was wrong.
Couldn't eat any of the $80 dinner and left feeling sick to our stomachs because of the emotional stress and embarrassment. This locations has real problems!

Update Feb 2018
Decide to try this location again.
Food was the same, 'good', and the utensils were there this time, before the food! Our server was changed before the food was brought and one of the meals was the wrong order - plate and utensils returned. This took 15 minutes to correct while everyone waited. Now we had cold food again. The correct food was brought with NO UTENSILS OR A SET MADE AVAILABLE! Asked the server TWO TIMES before a set was brought - took at least 6-7 minutes. I had asked for tea before we had ordered the food, and it arrived with the bill!
This location still has a lot to learn!</Text>< response>

< Review>
We just returned home from what was supposed to be a very special day -- a 26th anniversary. We are regulars in this place and have been for the last 3 years, but after today, I feel compelled to leave a very poor feedback. In the past, almost every visit starts with us asking for a lemon wedge so we can properly clean and disinfect the filthy, under-washed silverware. Today, in addition to that, my eggplant parmesan dish was under-cooked. It literally tasted and chewed like a hockey puck. They were re-doing it for 16 minutes. My wife was forced to eat her dish alone, and I lost my appetite completely. My wife and I were sitting in front of dirty dishes for another 11 minutes awaiting a manager. My special 26th anniversary was further destroy when Shawn Welch, the assistant general manager showed up at our table with an arrogant attitude and fake smile.< /Review>
<username>Polish Christopher< /username><Rate>1</Rate><userid>107784301607877886456< /userid><Date>1468625958865<//Date></record></dataset><record>
<user_id>105692744256480109238</user_id>< user_name>
Chelsea Madren (OC Food Diva)<//user_name>
<time>1428362388152</time><Rating>4</Rating>< Text>
Hibachi Steak is certified Angus beef hanger steak with shiitake mushrooms, onions, and bean sprouts served with wasabi mashed potatoes and tempura asparagus. The steak was a great cut, but I think it would have been better served as whole with the shiitake, onion, and bean sprout mixture on top. The sauce that everything was tossed in was overpowering whole plate. It would have been better as a marinade for the steak and let it caramelize on the grill. The wasabi mashed potatoes did not quite match. This would have paired better with fish like miso-glazed salmon. The tempura asparagus were cooked perfectly with a crispy, light batter while retaining the green flavor of the asparagus. Rating: 2/5

Grilled Rib-Eye Steak is served with French fries. I think a couple of tempura onion rings snuck onto my plate as well. The ribeye was grilled to a perfect rare. The meat was beautifully marbled for a juicy, tender steak. The fries were fried perfectly with a golden brown crispy outside and tender on the inside. The tempura onion rings were fantastic! The batter was light and crispy on the outside and the onion was sweet and tender inside. Rating: 5/5

Kobe Burger is an American style Kobe beef burger topped with saut√©ed mushrooms and onions. I can't eat a burger without cheese so I added a slice of cheddar. One of my friends had ordered it on a prior visit and she loved it. I love Wagyu beef so I knew the next time, I had to try it. It was cooked to a perfect medium rare, blending the grilled flavor on the outside and taste the sweet, buttery flavor of the meat inside. This burger was onolicious! It's one of the best burgers I've ever had. The mushrooms and onions were the perfect topping. I am glad that I went with a green salad instead of fries. This was a burger to finish in one sitting. Reheating it would not do it justice. Rating: 5/5

Chicken Madeira is saut√©ed chicken breast topped with fresh asparagus, melted mozzarella, mushroom Madeira sauce, and served with mashed potatoes. This is my hubby's favorite dish of all time! He has been ordering it since we started dating back in the early 1990s. The flavor is always consistent and he always orders it for dinner. The chicken was tender and soaked up the addictive Madeira sauce. The mushrooms acted like sponges and absorbed the sauce as well. The mashed potatoes were creamy and had just enough lumpy texture of potato and red potato skin. Rating: 5/5

Cappuccino is double espresso and foamy steamed milk. I'm not sure what kind of beans that they use or if I'm just used to coffee in Europe, but the espresso used was very bitter and acidic. Even with sugar, the bitter bite just hits you like a freight train. Rating: 2/5

Chocolate Chip Cookie-Dough Cheesecake is creamy cheesecake loaded with chocolate chip cookie-dough and walnuts. The cheesecake was creamy and silky. The cookie-dough added a granular sugar texture and flavor. The chocolate chips can be hard as they were in the refrigerator but melt down pretty quickly on the palate. I also loved the whipped cream dollops sprinkled with even more chocolate chips. Rating: 5/5

Adam's Peanut Butter Cup Fudge Ripple is creamy cheesecake swirled with caramel, peanut butter, Butterfinger and Reese's Peanut Butter Cups. This is also my hubby's favorite cheesecake. He orders this cheesecake probably 90% of the time. It has all of his favorite flavors in it: chocolate, caramel, and peanut butter. It was very rich and decadent. He will usually take it home and will take two to three sittings to finish it. It goes great with a hot cup of coffee. Rating: 5/5< /Text>

<Name>Alice Ly<//Name><Time>1398667501371< /Time><Rating>3< /Rating>< review>
I wouldn't necessarily volunteer to go to Cheesecake Factory if I had a choice but I've come here mostly for company lunches and if there's a gift card in the picture ;)

Notable dishes/items:

Ahi Tartare
Banana Cream Cheesecake
Chicken Bellagio
Coulotte Steak
Happy Hour Items
Meatloaf

Disliked:

Chinese Chicken Salad - completely bland, and the lettuce wasn't fresh

Waitstaff are all pretty friendly though and food comes out fairly quick!

I'm just not personally a fan of the food/prices in general :)

If anything, I'd come here solely for the BANANA CREAM CHEESECAKE. Yum!</review>
